    <p align="left">I have said it before and will say it again - &quot;Faction is
    everything!&quot;. If a quest is listed as open to &quot;all&quot; I automatically assume
    you know you have to be liked by the people in question.</p>
      <p align="left">For those of an evil persuasion this may be one of the most important
    locations in Norrath. A central home on Antonica without hassle. I have
      searched high and low for ways to improve faction here and can not find
      any way for a disliked person to improve anything but Indigo Brotherhood,
      the guards. This will allow you to walk through Nektulous Forest, but does
      not help with merchants an others.</p>
      <p align="left">To improve Indigo Brotherhood faction:<br>
      1. Kill the <a href="#Halfling Slaughter" target="_self">injured halfling</a>
      (level 16ish?) in Najena and turn in cap.<br>
      2. Kill the woodelf slaves (around level 5) located in Crushbone.<br>
      3. Killing the nobles (around level 14) in Innothule Swamp.<br>
      4. Giving red wine to the necro scribe at top of library (Lokar T'Biath is name)</p>
      <p align="left">This last one improves faction with the merchants.</p>
      <p align="left">If anyone knows of others I would appreciate a note. <a href="mailto:penance@eqguide.com">Penance</a></p>
