    <p align="left"><span class="qtitle">Title: <a name="Thex Mallet">Thex Mallet</a></span><br>
    <span class="qinfo">Items Needed:</span> 3 mallet pieces<br>
    <span class="qinfo">Items Rewarded:</span> Thex Mallet (1hb, delay 33, dam 5, +5 vs.
    magic, Weight 8.5) or turn in for random loot<br>
    <span class="qinfo">Class/Race:</span> all<br>
    <span class="qinfo">Confirmed:</span> No</p>
    <p align="left"><span class="qinfo">Description and Comments: </span>Once you have
    completed the Sir Lindeal quest Loveal may send you on this one. Step one is a password
    phrase (Utalk Adarev Otcin) to Kizdean Gix in West Commons. He will give you a note to
    give to Hubard L'rod. He is the skeleton in Befallen. Well seems Mr. Gix is unaware poor
    Hubard is dead. Makes no difference though as he still takes the note and talks to you.
    Giving this note to L'rod spawns Commander Windstream. He holds the combining piece to the
    Mallet. The other 2 pieces are found randomly on the elf skeleton located past the door
    into the 3rd floor area. This weapon is basically a better deal than the reward and can
    probably be sold or used much more efficiently than the reward for turning it in. Then
    again who would want to purposely piss off the Queen by wielding her mallet...
    However the belief is that turning this in triggers the Ring of the Dead quest. Sources
    differ on whether this casts bind affinity or gate. Until I see one I don't believe
    anything I read.</p>
